library(colorRamps)
library(tidyverse)
##  Attaching core tidyverse packages  tidyverse 2.0.0 
##  forcats   1.0.0      stringr   1.5.1
##  lubridate 1.9.4      tibble    3.2.1
##  purrr     1.0.4      tidyr     1.3.1
##  readr     2.1.5
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
##  dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
##  dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
##  dplyr::where()  masks ape::where()
##  Use the conflicted package (<http://conflicted.r-lib.org/>) to force all conflicts to become errors
data0<-read.csv("N02ARG.csv",row.names = 1)
env0 <- read.csv("N02group.csv",row.names = 1)
#ID0<- amf.ID.rarify
da.rar <- t(data0)
da.rar<-as.data.frame(da.rar)
env <- env0
env0$Nitrogen<-as.factor(env0$Nitrogen)


data<-merge(env0,da.rar,by="row.names")
data1<-data[,-(1:8)]
group1<-data[,(1:8)]
set.seed(315)
adonis_result<-adonis2(data1 ~ Nhistory + Nlevel + Nhistory:Nlevel, 
                       data = group1, 
                       permutations = 9999,
                       by = "terms")  # 

adonis_annotate <- adonis_result %>%
  rownames_to_column("term") %>%  # 
  filter(!term %in% c("Residual", "Total")) %>%  # 
  mutate(
    term = gsub("Nhistory:Nlevel", "NhistoryNlevel", term),  # 
    # P
    p_formatted = ifelse(
      `Pr(>F)` < 0.001,  # P0.001
      format(`Pr(>F)`, scientific = TRUE, digits = 3),  # 
      round(`Pr(>F)`, 3)  # 3
    ),
    # 
    label = paste0(term, ": R=", round(R2, 3), ", P=", p_formatted)
  ) %>%
  pull(label)  # 
set.seed(315)
bac.pc<-pcoa(vegdist(decostand(da.rar,"hellinger"),"bray"))
envpc<-data.frame( env, bac.pc$vectors)
pc1=round(bac.pc$values$Relative_eig[1], 3)*100
pc2=round(bac.pc$values$Relative_eig[2], 3)*100
envpc$Nhistory<-factor(envpc$Nhistory,levels = c("Ncont","Ncess"))
envpc$Nitrogen<-factor(envpc$Nitrogen,levels=c("0","2","5","10","15","20","50"),ordered = T)
col11<-c("darkgrey","chartreuse","deepskyblue","darkviolet","darkorange","#CC0033","darkgoldenrod")
lines<-c("Ncont"="dotted","Ncess"="solid")
shap = c("Ncont" = 19, "Ncess" = 17)
p1<-ggplot(data=envpc, aes(x= Axis.1 , y= Axis.2,colour = as.factor(envpc$Nlevel),linetype=Nhistory,shape=Nhistory))+ 
  #facet_wrap(~Nitrogen)+
  geom_point(aes(colour=as.factor(envpc$Nlevel),shape=Nhistory),alpha = 0.8,size=10)+
  stat_ellipse(aes( colour= as.factor(envpc$Nlevel)),level = 0.5, show.legend = T)+
  # 
  scale_colour_manual(values=col11,
                      labels=c(expression(0),expression(2),
                               expression(5),expression(10),
                               expression(15),expression(20),
                               expression(50)
                      )
  )+
  scale_linetype_manual(
    values = lines,  # manualvalueslines
    labels = c(
      expression(N[cont]),
      expression(N[cess])
    )
  ) +
  # Nadd
  scale_shape_manual(
    values = shap,
    labels = c(
      expression(N[cont]),  # Ncont -> N_cont
      expression(N[cess])   # Ncess -> N_cess
    )
  ) +
  labs(x = sprintf("PCo1 (%.1f%%)", pc1), y = sprintf("PCo2 (%.1f%%)", pc2))+
  theme_bw()+guides(
    colour = guide_legend(title = expression(N[level])),
    shape = guide_legend(title = expression(N[history])),    # Nadd -> N_add
    linetype = guide_legend(title = expression(N[history]))  # 
  ) +
  theme(text=element_text(size=16,  family="serif"))+
  theme(text=element_text(size=20,  family="sans", face="bold"))+
  theme(legend.title = element_text(colour="black", size=16, face="bold"),
        legend.text = element_text(colour="black", size=16, face="bold"),
        axis.text=element_text(size=16,face="bold"),
        axis.title=element_text(size=16,face="bold"))+
  annotate("text",
           x = mean(range(envpc$Axis.1)),  # x
           y = max(envpc$Axis.2) * 1.1,    # y
           label = "Antibiotic resistance genes (ARG)",
           hjust = 0.5,  # 
           vjust = 0,    # 
           size = 6,     # 
           fontface = "bold",  # 
           color = "black")
p1<-p1+theme(panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA,color = "black",size=1.5,linetype = "solid"))
